# Image Properties

Images elements also have properties that can change their style.

## Size
One of the image properties is size. You can control size of an image using the `width` and `height` properties. The size is determined by the number of pixels tall and wide an image is. Pixels is abbreviated to `px`.  For example to make all the images 100 pixels wide you would use:

<pre>
img {
	width: 100px;
}
</pre>

Although you can control both width and height it is best practice to only set either width and height since setting both can distort the image.



## Borders
Borders are a common property for many elements including images. Borders consist of three properties: `border-style`, `border-width` and `border-color`.

<pre>
img {
      border-style: dashed;
      border-width: 5px;
      border-color: blue;
}
</pre>

For more information about borders go to <a href="http://www.w3schools.com/css/css_border.asp"> W3 Schools - Border Properties</a>.

# Do This

* Add a rule to style img elements
* Use the rule to set the width of all images to 200 pixels
* Add borders to all images. Be creative and try different border styles and colors.

