# Background Color

Another common CSS property used to style pages is `background-color`. This property will set the background color of a specific element.  You can use any of the CSS colors for background color.

For example the code below will set the text color of all h1 elements to blue and the background color to red.

<pre>
h1 {
	color: blue;
	background-color: red;
}
</pre>

# Do This
Try out the `background-color` property with paragraphs.

* Give all the paragraphs (`<p>`) elements a background color of your choice.

